37:58.480 --> 38:01.199
Let's make The Luncheonette sail
once agaIn.

38:01.340 --> 38:03.615
I'm in.

38:04.520 --> 38:05.589
I'm in.

38:05.730 --> 38:07.300
- Are you serious?
- I'm serious.

38:07.450 --> 38:09.133
You're--'cause I--
it's too much for me to--

38:09.280 --> 38:11.453
Unwavering.
I'm in.

38:11.590 --> 38:12.727
We're gonna make
The Luncheonette work.

38:12.870 --> 38:14.007
- You promise?
- I promise you. Okay?

38:14.150 --> 38:14.969
- Okay.
- You okay?

38:15.120 --> 38:16.451
- Yes.
- You sure?

38:16.600 --> 38:18.909
- Yes. Yes, yes, yes. Thank you.
- All right.

38:19.050 --> 38:20.460
Thank you.

38:20.600 --> 38:22.841
It's gonna work.

38:30.720 --> 38:32.574
Hi.

38:32.720 --> 38:34.164
- Hey, Dad, what--
- Oh, my God.

38:34.310 --> 38:35.447
Hey.

38:35.580 --> 38:37.229
What are you--
What are you doing here?

38:37.380 --> 38:39.166
Look who it is.

38:39.310 --> 38:40.754
I heard there were some major
world-class speed skaters here.

38:40.900 --> 38:41.650
- I wanted to--
- He's getting better.

38:41.800 --> 38:42.960
- Yeah.
- Is he?

38:43.110 --> 38:44.316
- A little bit better.
- Because of me.

38:44.460 --> 38:45.176
- Because of you?
- Dad, Dad, look.

38:45.320 --> 38:46.173
A little better,
she's right.

38:46.320 --> 38:47.139
All right.
Let's see it.

38:47.290 --> 38:49.929
Okay. I'll see you soon.

38:50.080 --> 38:52.219
[The War on Drugs'
Eyes to the Wind]

38:52.360 --> 38:55.215
[upbeat music]

39:03.030 --> 39:06.124
[The War on Drugs]
I was sailing down here
on the wind

39:09.170 --> 39:12.094
When I met you

39:12.240 --> 39:14.583
And I fell away again

39:15.560 --> 39:18.939
Whoa. Look.

39:19.080 --> 39:22.789
Like a train in reverse
down a dark road

39:24.910 --> 39:26.389
Carrying the whole load

39:26.530 --> 39:27.974
Oh, my gosh.

39:28.120 --> 39:31.009
Just rattling
the whole way home

39:31.160 --> 39:32.297
[Zeek]
Millie.

39:32.430 --> 39:33.988
Yeah, I'm in here.

39:34.130 --> 39:35.392
Come and look at these pictures
that Max developed.

39:35.540 --> 39:37.576
No, later, later.
I'm just way too excited.

39:37.720 --> 39:40.951
I remembered what happened
to my Reggie Jackson baseball.

39:41.100 --> 39:42.260
Will you let it
pull you in?

39:42.410 --> 39:43.263
- Oh.
- Yeah.

39:43.410 --> 39:44.923
You remember
Adam and Crosby

39:45.070 --> 39:46.378
used to play with it
all the time,

39:46.520 --> 39:47.964
so I took it,
and I put it in a shoe box,

39:48.100 --> 39:50.443
and I hid it up in the rafters
in the old barn.

39:50.590 --> 39:52.103
So we got to go back
to the old house.

39:52.250 --> 39:53.694
Come on.

39:53.830 --> 39:54.558
Okay.

39:54.700 --> 39:55.485
- Come on.
- [laughs]

39:55.630 --> 39:59.214
Babe

39:59.360 --> 40:01.180
Let me hold you

40:09.440 --> 40:11.294
They painted.

40:11.440 --> 40:12.771
Yeah.

40:12.920 --> 40:14.091
I never would have thought
of that color,

40:14.230 --> 40:15.504
but it looks good.

40:15.650 --> 40:18.198
[children chattering]

40:19.720 --> 40:22.587
[upbeat music]

40:58.170 --> 41:00.343
[both laughing]

41:00.490 --> 41:03.175
Boy, she's got
her hands full.

41:03.320 --> 41:06.073
Yeah, I hope
she's loving every second of it.

41:11.640 --> 41:15.394
So...go knock on the door.

41:15.540 --> 41:16.677
Oh, my God.

41:20.020 --> 41:22.909
- [exhales]
- What?

41:23.060 --> 41:26.120
I changed my mind.

41:26.270 --> 41:27.498
'Cause someday,

41:27.650 --> 41:28.787
those kids are gonna be playing
hide-and-seek

41:28.930 --> 41:30.989
or messing around
in the barn,

41:31.140 --> 41:34.132
and they're gonna find an old
shoe box full of baseball stuff,

41:34.280 --> 41:36.066
and they're gonna--

41:36.210 --> 41:38.929
they're gonna think
they found a hidden treasure.

41:39.080 --> 41:41.594
It's gonna be the best day
of their lives.

41:45.530 --> 41:47.805
Sure.

41:47.950 --> 41:50.009
Yeah.

41:50.160 --> 41:51.673
Yeah, let's go home.
